GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 285
Short Title: Funds for Laurinburg-Maxton Airport. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative G. Pierce.
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Appropriations, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
March 6, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FUNDS FOR LAURINBURG-MAXTON AIRPORT.
3 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
4 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the Highway Fund to the Department of
5 Transportation, Division of Aviation, the sum of fifty-two million five hundred thousand dollars
6 ($52,500,000) in nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be allocated to Southeast
7 Regional Airport Authority to be used according to the following schedule:
8 Runway 5/23 Extension $28,000,000
9 Airport Capital Projects $15,000,000
10 Water & Sewer Capital Projects $9,500,000
11 SECTION 2. The Division shall submit a quarterly report on the use of funds to the
12 Joint Legislative Transportation Oversight Committee and the Fiscal Research Division.
13 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*H285-v-1*

